  "biosensor": {
    "description": "An engineered Salmonella for tumor immunotherapy: a hypoxia sensor (pepT promoter, activated under low oxygen in tumor core) drives a Flp recombinase. Flp excises a transcriptional terminator flanked by FRT sites, permanently activating a downstream pTac promoter driving flagellin B (FljB, a potent TLR5 agonist for immune activation). A second module: constitutive pJ23100 drives an anti-CD47 nanobody (blocking the don't-eat-me signal) fused to an OmpA surface display anchor. A third module: arabinose-inducible MazF toxin as external kill switch.",
